from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql.functions import col, lit, trim, upper, coalesce, concat_ws, xxhash64
from delta.tables import DeltaTable
import time

# Initialize Spark with proper Delta Lake support
spark = SparkSession.builder \
    .appName("FixHashId") \
    .config("spark.sql.extensions", "io.delta.sql.DeltaSparkSessionExtension") \
    .config("spark.sql.catalog.spark_catalog", "org.apache.spark.sql.delta.catalog.DeltaCatalog") \
    .getOrCreate()

# Your Delta table path
delta_path = "abfss://dl-juror-eric-voters-temp@baubaisadfsaprod.dfs.core.windows.net/voters_deduplicated_delta"

# Load the Delta table
print(f"Loading Delta table from {delta_path}")
delta_table = DeltaTable.forPath(spark, delta_path)
full_df = delta_table.toDF()

# Option 1: Fix only the specific list of known bad hash_ids
df_bad = full_df.filter(col("hash_id").isin(bad_hash_ids))

# Option 2: Fix ANY hash_ids that contain underscores (which suggests they're malformed)
# Uncomment this line instead to fix all malformed hash_ids
#df_bad = full_df.filter(col("hash_id").contains("_"))

# Count the bad hash IDs found
bad_count = df_bad.count()
print(f"Found {bad_count} records with bad hash_ids to fix")

if bad_count == 0:
    print("No bad hash_ids found. Exiting.")
    exit(0)

# Sample of records to be updated
print("Sample of records to be updated:")
df_bad.select("hash_id", "fname", "lname", "address").show(5, truncate=False)

# Function to generate the correct hash_id
def generate_hash_id(df):
    """Generate hash_id using all standard fields"""
    return df.withColumn(
        "new_hash_id",
        xxhash64(
            concat_ws(
                "||",
                trim(coalesce(col("register_lett"), lit(""))),
                trim(coalesce(col("poll_number"), lit(""))),
                upper(trim(coalesce(col("fname"), lit("")))),
                upper(trim(coalesce(col("lname"), lit("")))),
                trim(coalesce(col("rec_num"), lit(""))),
                trim(coalesce(col("zip"), lit(""))),
                trim(coalesce(col("address"), lit("")))
            )
        )
    )

# Apply the hash ID generation to bad records
print("Generating new hash_ids...")
df_fixed = generate_hash_id(df_bad)

# Show the changes (old vs new)
print("Sample of hash_id changes (old vs new):")
df_fixed.select("hash_id", "new_hash_id").show(5, False)

# Create a mapping dataframe from old hash_id to new hash_id along with all columns for matching
matching_columns = ["register_lett", "poll_number", "fname", "lname", "rec_num", "address", "zip"]
df_update_map = df_fixed.select(*matching_columns, col("new_hash_id"))

# Create temporary view for merge
df_update_map.createOrReplaceTempView("hash_id_updates")

# Perform the merge - match on all identifying columns
print(f"Updating {bad_count} records in the Delta table...")
start_time = time.time()

try:
    delta_table.alias("target").merge(
        source=spark.table("hash_id_updates").alias("source"),
        condition=" AND ".join([f"target.{col} = source.{col}" for col in matching_columns])
    ).whenMatchedUpdate(
        set={"hash_id": "source.new_hash_id"}
    ).execute()
    
    end_time = time.time()
    print(f" Successfully updated {bad_count} hash_ids in {end_time - start_time:.2f} seconds")
    
    # Verify the update worked
    post_update_bad = delta_table.toDF().filter(col("hash_id").isin(bad_hash_ids)).count()
    print(f"Verification: {post_update_bad} bad hash_ids remaining in the table")
    
except Exception as e:
    print(f" Error updating hash_ids: {str(e)}")
    import traceback
    print(traceback.format_exc())
